messages.text: Hey, what’s happening up there? No one’s answering on my headset.
Voice communication is down. We’re working to get it back.
Ten foot waves are rocking the ship like a toy..but other than, that we’re good.
How’s the view from the sub?
Dark, forbidding and beautiful. Everything outside my little window looks so alien.
Whoa! Something big just swam past.
I’m too deep for squid. Weird.
I'm fine :) This is what we live for, right?
If it means anything, you’re officially at 27,000 feet. That’s the deepest any woman has ever been.
I’m sure half the planet disagrees with that statement.
And the record is 35,000 feet. Male or female. That’s the record.
I’m seeing a spike in radiation.
Something very big. It nearly rolled me.
What the hell could roll a ten ton sub?
Whatever it was knocked out a few systems too.
Give it a minute. Let me try and get back on line.
No can do. Whatever hit me knocked out all external systems. I have text-to-com and one outside light still working.
Can’t see how if life support is up.
God dammit! You’re falling past 30,000 and going way too fast!
Stay calm up there. I’m the one in the can.
Shit. Maya.. you’re drifting.. the light that’s still working.. is it on your window side?
Sonar has you descending at an angle.
I see it.. coming up on the canyon wall fast.
There’s no time.. im gonna hit.
Don’t hit the glass don’t hit the glass don’t hit the glass hang on
The sphere isn’t breeched so it could be worse. But I lost voice-to-text and interior lights. Communicating manually now.
I have no systems to do that with.
No. Headed straight down but I’m on my side.
How long till the bottom? Enough time to reboot?
No, you’re gonna hit soon and you’re gonna hit hard. HANG ON!
I think so. At least I’m not falling anymore.
Want the good news or the bad?
I’m staring up at an overhang of rock above the sphere.
I was counting on you for that. ☹
Well…looks like you rolled into a ditch. You’re at 36,006 feet down.
Maya, this is serious. We need to figure out how to get you back.
Nothing to figure. I reboot and pray the ballast release comes back online.
Negative. You don’t know what kind of damage you sustained. If the systems don’t come back up, you lose life support. Captain says to wait on the fail safe.
No. It’ll take three more hours for the salt water to corrode the galvanic plates and release the air bags.
Life support took a jolt when I hit bottom. I lost heat and CO2 scrubbers.
Fail safe takes three hours minimum. I’ll be dead in two.
And what if it doesn’t reboot?
But that won’t change how much I love you.
Bullshit, Maya. Don’t you dare say goodbye.
I’m not. I’m simply saying how much I love you.
And whether or not I ever feel the sun on my face again, you will remain the most brilliant, fascinating and loving man I have ever known.
Maya, don’t. Let’s look at every options.
0 options. But I trust completely in this ship.. the ship you’ve built to bring me back home. So…☺
God dammit, that’s not fair. How could you do that?!
How could you cut me off without letting me say goodbye?
Without letting me tell you how badly I want you to come back?
How much I NEED you to come back.
Why would you go without letting me tell you I love?
Gonna strangle you when you get here.
Not worried. Be home in time for dinner.
Captain says you should be worried.. about what caused this.
That’s for him to worry about. ☺
What scares me is the fact that whatever it was didn’t show up on sonar.
